# Documentation Maintenance

**BRD / HLD / LLD:** See **`.cursor/rules/brd-hld-lld-on-request-only.mdc`** — those three files are **not** updated on every iteration; only when the user asks.

**All other substantive code, config, or database changes** (per the table below) should still be reflected in the relevant documentation in the same change set (or immediately after, if the user explicitly splits work). Do not leave behavior, APIs, flows, or schema undocumented where this rule still applies.

## Canonical documents (under `Documentation/`)

| Document | Purpose | When to update |
|----------|---------|----------------|
| **`business-requirements-document.md`** (BRD) | Business rules, functional requirements, §6.1a Siebel SOP | Any user-visible or business-meaningful flow/rule change; changelog rows for notable updates |
| **`high-level-design.md`** (HLD) | Backend modules, client pages, architecture changelog | New/changed modules, pages, or major flow; add **changelog** row when behavior contract shifts |
| **`low-level-design.md`** (LLD) | APIs, module layout, Playwright/Siebel parity (**§2.4d**), **changelog** (e.g. **6.x**) | Endpoint/service changes; automation sequence or helper semantics; **always** add/update **LLD changelog** for non-trivial Siebel/DMS behavior |
| **`Database DDL.md`** | Tables, columns, relationships | Any **`DDL/`** script or **column/table/schema** change only — update table definitions and changelog; **do not** add changelog rows for automation-only or API-only work with no database change |
| **`technical-architecture.md`** | Repo layout, §6 doc maintenance | Optional: bump §7 changelog when §6 maintenance policy changes |
| **`checkpoints.md`** | Canonical index of named git checkpoints (serial no., name, tag, commit, IST date, TODOs) | **Whenever a checkpoint is created** — append a table row in the same session; see **`.cursor/rules/checkpoints-registry.mdc`** |

## Mapping (quick reference)

- **New API endpoint or router** → LLD (API Endpoints table), HLD (backend modules)
- **New DB table or column** → `DDL/` script, `Database DDL.md`
- **New business rule or constraint** → BRD (Business Rules / relevant §)
- **New page, flow, or feature** → BRD (FRs), HLD (client pages, data flow)
- **New or changed service / repository** → HLD (backend modules), LLD (module layout)
- **Siebel / Fill DMS / `prepare_vehicle` / Playwright behavior** → BRD §6.1a if SOP meaning changes; LLD §2.4d + **LLD changelog**; HLD `fill_hero_dms_service` row if module contract changes
- **Pure automation refactor** (no API/DB) → LLD + BRD as applicable; **Database DDL.md** — **N/A** unless `DDL/` or schema docs change

## Agent checklist

Before finishing a task that touched `backend/`, `client/`, `DDL/`, or DMS/Siebel flows: confirm which docs above were updated or explicitly N/A (**Database DDL.md** only when schema/DDL changed). **BRD / HLD / LLD:** N/A by default unless the user requested an update to those files.

**If the task created or named a git checkpoint / milestone tag:** confirm **`Documentation/checkpoints.md`** was updated or explicitly N/A (N/A only when no checkpoint was created).

Reference: `Documentation/technical-architecture.md` §6 Documentation Maintenance.
